doc_summary_long: The U.S. government is still trying to figure out who carried out the massive cyberattack that crippled popular websites around the globe last week. 'We don't have any idea who did that,' President Barack Obama said on 'Jimmy Kimmel Live!' The perpetrators caused widespread disruption by bombarding a key backbone of the internet with so much traffic that it impairs normal service, a method known as a denial of service attack.
doc_summary_short: The U.S. government is still trying to figure out who carried out the massive cyberattack that crippled popular websites around the globe last week.
doc_title: Obama: We have no idea who carried out huge cyberattack
